news.title: SC directs Chandigarh administration to refund Rs 47.75 crore to Parsvnath Developers' subsidiary
news.para: The Chandigarh administration could not hand over the possession of the land to PFCL in terms of the said development agreement. The PFCL had sought refund of the allotment money paid, along with compensation.

news.title: Smartworks, Table Space to lease over two million sq ft in Delhi & Mumbai
news.para: While Table Space is in the final stages to sign around 500,000 sq ft across three centres with DLF and Godrej in Gurgaon and with Bharti at Aerocity, Smartworks is in talks with Tata Realty and Hiranandani in Mumbai.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board releases new building bye-laws
news.para: A new feature of the new bye-laws is the division of the cantonment into four distinct zones, each with specific development parameters.

news.title: Blackstone closes $10.8 billion European property fund amid market turmoil
news.para: The fundraise for the Europe Real Estate Partners VII fund is the largest ever pool of external capital amassed for European property, Blackstone said.

news.title: Karnataka minister orders crackdown on illegal sand mining in Haveri
news.para: At Tuesday's KDP meeting, the minister addressed the prevalent issue of illegal sand mining in the district. He noted widespread unauthorised sand extraction from the Varada and Tungabhadra rivers.

news.title: Telangana's IT park plan threatens green spaces
news.para: After a Supreme Court suo motu intervention, and a stay on all 'development' activity until further orders, Telangana CM Revanth Reddy has reportedly dropped the IT park project and now proposes an 'eco park'

news.title: Goa government to streamline sand and laterite mining permissions
news.para: Sawant held a review meeting with the officials of the directorate of mines and geology and the environment department to streamline the process of granting permission for minor minerals and resolve issues related to major minerals.

news.title: Lucknow development body demolishes Palm Residency in Sushant Golf City
news.para: The illegal colony was being developed over nearly 38 acres of land in Bakkas village. The colony was being developed without any layout approval from the LDA. Roads, drains, boundary walls and a site office had already came up on the site.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to conduct aerial GIS survey
news.para: Once the DGCA grants permission, the aircraft will follow predetermined flight paths to ensure comprehensive coverage of the municipal area.

news.title: Trichy civic body offer 5% incentive on property tax till April 30
news.para: There are 2.4 lakh property tax assessments in the city, and corporation annually generates around 137 crore as revenue.

news.title: How Accurate are Home Loan Calculators?
news.para: Although Home Loan calculators are a great tool for estimating your eligibility and potential EMIs, they should be used as a guideline. Such calculators are widely used and give the user the opportunity to quickly determine affordability and budget.

news.title: Rajasthan: RHB to launch new housing schemes in five districts
news.para: As part of the schemes, the board will offer both flats and independent houses for various income groups, including EWS, LIG, MIG, and HIG.

news.title: Kolkata records 9% growth in office rentals in Q1 2025
news.para: Despite this decrease, the city's average transacted office rents rose by 9%, reaching Rs 42/sq ft/month — the highest among the top eight cities, alongside Hyderabad.

news.title: Jharkhand government announces new townships across eight cities to address urban housing needs
news.para: The department of urban development and housing has begun the groundwork for this ambitious project under which around 400 to 500 acres of land will be acquired in each location.

news.title: RBI cuts repo rate by 25 basis points
news.para: As expected, the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC), which consists of three RBI and three external members, cut the repo rate by 25 basis points to 6.00%.

news.title: Delhi: DDA extends deadline for two housing schemes till April 30
news.para: DDA stated on Tuesday that bookings under both schemes would now reopen from April 9 and continue till April 30 midnight. "The remaining unsold flats will be available for booking,"

news.title: Maharashtra government to promote artificial sand usage
news.para: The use of m-sand or manufactured sand will be subsequently made compulsory, a statement from the Chief Minister's Office stated.

news.title: hBits gets SEBI's nod to launch its SM REIT
news.para: The company plans to launch its maiden SM REIT IPO by June. Over the next few weeks, hBits will also migrate its existing portfolio of commercial properties into the SM REIT structure.

news.title: Delhi government plans to renovate distribute 52,000 flats to slum-dwellers
news.para: ​​​A fund of Rs 700 crore in the Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) has been allocated to Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) for the welfare of those residing in slums,"

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves joint redevelopment of two MHADA layouts in Mumbai
news.para: The cabinet approved a floor space index (FSI) of four for the redevelopment. Mhada will get housing stock equivalent to one FSI in both layouts.
